## Analysis of `pcap_lookupdev`

The `pcap_lookupdev` function is a legacy function in the pcap library used to find a suitable network interface for packet capture. It attempts to return the name of the first non-loopback network device available on the system.

### Task 1: Functionality Description

`pcap_lookupdev` attempts to find and return the name of a suitable network device for packet capture. It first enumerates all available network devices using `pcap_findalldevs`. If no devices are found, or if the first device listed is a loopback interface (implying no non-loopback devices are available), it reports an error and returns `NULL`. Otherwise, it returns the name of the first non-loopback device found. This function is deprecated and not supported when `pcap_init()` has been called, as it is not thread-safe and its behavior can be inconsistent, especially on Windows.

